The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal denies that former eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede will chair the Cooperative Governance portfolio committee. eNCA's Thuba Vilane has more. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC's National Executive Committee, is expected to sit this weekend with the issue of leaders with dented reputations, set to be discussed. The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal has denied that former eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede will chair the Cooperative Governance portfolio committee. Last week Gumede, who is facing corruption charges, was sworn in as a member of the legislature. READ: ANC calls DA's claims about Gumede 'political hallucination The ANC says Gumede is just an ordinary member, for now. The DA claimed she is tasked with chairing the Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Portfolio Committee. "It is worse when that someone has failed to lead the municipality. Then you give a person a position to chair the portfolio committee of Cogta, where she has to look after all municipalities in KZN", DA KZN's Zwakele Mncwango said. The ANC is criticised because Gumede is currently in court over fraud and corruption charges, but the party is accusing the DA of political point-scoring. READ: ANC Veterans object to Gumede redeployment One political analyst says Gumede is no different from other ANC leaders because there are many in government positions with tainted images. Watch the video above for more on this story.